column5: Well, I guess I sat on a lucky horseshoe, because I got offered (by a work contractor) an expense-paid trip for 3 days to the Northend Outpost. Just saw online it's over $1,100/person for this trip!  Anybody been? I'm assuming I can catch my fill of walleye with nothing but 4" grubs and jigs or even cigarette butts?  Can't believe my boss and wife are letting me go.
I'm registering an official complaint. No-one, I mean no-one should be THAT lucky!
You going soon? And I agree with HTHM
Every once in a while you're the windshield instead of the bug  Congrats and have a blast
Next weekend I'll be there. Awaiting final confirmation tomorrow. It's still setting in.
Bring warm clothes. Its gonna be yucky this weekend but looks like things should be settled for next.  yellow jigs  do you fly out of Hawk or White River
Warm clothes...check. Yellow jigs...check.  White River.
Camera....check.....   Right on bud! Have a good time and take lots of pics!
What dates are you actually going?  My brother is heading up there as well, with work.
Would like to click the "like" icon on this one.  Nice win, have fun.  Can't tell ya anything about the lake itself but can just imagine the fish waiting for ya.
thems some big horseshoes you got this year dood - don't fall out of the boat........ you'll sink You also have  a very understanding wife    Enjoy, and look forward to the report
